> @dhwanikatagade, is it worth adding a note to the "Building IDE" section in the readme?

@ijuma - Once this change is applied I only have to run the `./gradlew eclipse` command. Would you want me to add notes to the README explaining that the build output goes to build_eclipse and why?

> the only issue I get is a compilation error in streams
> Description	Resource	Path	Location	Type
> Type mismatch: cannot convert from KeyValue<capture#27-of ? extends K1,V> to KeyValue<K1,V>	KStreamImpl.java	/streams/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/streams/kstream/internals	line 145	Java Problem
> curious what that is

@edoardocomar - This is due to an Eclipse issue that is observed even without the the changes in place. I just have to add a cast as a local change as follows to get it working. 
```
-                        return new KeyValue<>(mapper.apply(key, value), value);
+                        return (KeyValue<K1, V>) new KeyValue<>(mapper.apply(key, value), value);
```
I have known this issue in Eclipse where the maven build would work, IntelliJ would not report any errors, yet Eclipse would complain.
